Patry 2014-02-28T00:00:00Z The apartment is in a good location, close to Vatican City. Sant'Angelo and Ottaviano Metro stop are within walking distance. You are in the center of Rome in just a few minutes. There are also any bus stop for the other districts or trains for the airports Roma Termini, Fiumicino and Ciampino. The house is in a small building with three levels without a lift, clean, and there is a clean bathroom and a kitchenette. You have to share the apartment with three other girls. The house is bright and overlooks a small garden with trees from where you can see the Basilica of St. Peter, but there are no shops. Around the corner there is pharmacy, restaurant, pizzeria and a small supermarket. We share kitchen with one girl for breakfast, while another girl cooks in the evening at all hours and does not keep area clean. The fridge is always very messy. Plus, we share the apartment with two cats, there are two baskets of water and a litter box in the kitchen. The apartment is quiet and empty. 10-15 minutes walk there are several restaurants with pizza from 4 €
